org.knime.core.node.workflow

Interface ScopeStartNode<T extends FlowScopeContext>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - parameterized on the particular scope context implementation
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LoopStartNode, LoopStartNodeTerminator, LoopStartParallelizeNode
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BWElimLoopStartNodeModel, ColumnListLoopStartNodeModel, ColumnListLoopStartNodeModel, GenericTryNodeModel, GroupLoopStartNodeModel, LoopStartChunkNodeModel, LoopStartCountNodeModel, LoopStartGenericNodeModel, LoopStartIntervalNodeModel, LoopStartVariableNodeModel, RecursiveLoopStart2NodeModel, RecursiveLoopStartNodeModel, XValidatePartitionModel

    public interface ScopeStartNode<T extends FlowScopeContext>
    Interface implemented by NodeModel classes to define a the start of a new scope. The framework will take care of the details, in this case making sure variables put onto the stack inside the scope are removed when leaving it again. Derivatives of this interface, such as LoopStartNode add functionality on top of the scope.
    Since:
    2.8
    Author:
    M. Berthold, University of Konstanz & Bernd Wiswedel, KNIME.com
